WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.087
- Previously on
"Superman & Lois"...

00:04.129 --> 00:05.255
- Your mom wanted us
to move to Smallville.

00:05.296 --> 00:06.464
- This family needs Smallville.

00:06.506 --> 00:07.632
- What happened on my world

00:07.674 --> 00:08.883
is already happening
on this one.

00:08.925 --> 00:10.385
- It's very possible

00:10.427 --> 00:12.137
that Morgan Edge
is building an army.

00:12.178 --> 00:13.430
- You are putting
Kryptonian consciousnesses

00:13.471 --> 00:14.931
into people's bodies.

00:14.973 --> 00:17.142
You are taking them over
and giving them powers.

00:17.183 --> 00:18.435
[dramatic music]

00:18.476 --> 00:19.436
- Something happened
to me tonight.

00:19.477 --> 00:20.645
I blacked out.

00:20.687 --> 00:22.063
I don't know what's going on.

00:22.105 --> 00:23.732
- Did Morgan Edge
make you an offer?

00:23.773 --> 00:25.233
- I think it's time
you learned the truth

00:25.275 --> 00:26.526
about who I am

00:26.568 --> 00:29.029
and where I'm really from,
brother.

00:29.070 --> 00:30.947
♪ ♪

00:30.989 --> 00:33.950
[ethereal music]

00:33.992 --> 00:41.082
♪ ♪

00:42.208 --> 00:43.960
- Brother?

00:44.002 --> 00:46.087
- I know how unlikely
it may seem,

00:46.129 --> 00:47.505
but the two of us,

00:47.547 --> 00:49.883
we share the same
Kryptonian blood.

00:49.924 --> 00:51.509
- You are not my brother.

00:51.551 --> 00:53.219
- I am, Kal-El.

01:01.686 --> 01:04.314
My real name is Tal-Rho.

01:04.355 --> 01:06.649
I'm the son of Zeta-Rho

01:06.691 --> 01:08.401
and Lara Lor-Van.

01:08.443 --> 01:09.903
- That's not possible.

01:10.445 --> 01:11.821
My mother--

01:11.863 --> 01:14.574
- Married Jor-El, your father.
Yes, I know.

01:14.616 --> 01:16.826
Years after

01:16.868 --> 01:18.870
she'd been matched
to my father,

01:18.912 --> 01:21.039
years after I was born.

01:21.081 --> 01:22.582
It was when she first warned

01:22.624 --> 01:25.335
that Krypton was dying.

01:25.376 --> 01:28.505
The very reason
my father sent me here.

01:29.255 --> 01:32.342
I was the first
son of Krypton to leave...

01:33.968 --> 01:36.262
And I came here
with one purpose:

01:36.304 --> 01:38.348
to further
our Kryptonian heritage.

01:38.389 --> 01:39.349
[grunts]

01:39.390 --> 01:41.101
[dramatic music]

01:41.142 --> 01:42.894
- My mother

01:42.936 --> 01:44.395
would never destroy
innocent lives.

01:44.437 --> 01:45.897
- [laughs]

01:45.939 --> 01:47.941
Humans are far from innocent.

01:48.817 --> 01:50.777
- Jacob!
Oh, my God.

01:50.819 --> 01:52.612
- Margaret!
- It's a boy!

01:52.654 --> 01:53.696
- Don't you move.

01:53.738 --> 01:56.449
♪ ♪

01:56.491 --> 01:57.826
I said don't move!

01:57.867 --> 01:58.868
- [yelps]

01:58.910 --> 02:00.787
- This world you protect

02:00.829 --> 02:02.997
deserved better than those
who inhabited it.

02:03.039 --> 02:05.125
- That's not
your decision to make.

02:05.166 --> 02:07.252
- It's already been made.

02:08.753 --> 02:10.672
Don't you see, Kal?

02:10.713 --> 02:13.341
This is our chance

02:13.383 --> 02:14.759
to be with our own,

02:14.801 --> 02:16.219
to have a family again.

02:16.261 --> 02:17.929
- A family?

02:17.971 --> 02:19.556
- The mines, the X-Kryptonite,
the people in this town,

02:19.597 --> 02:22.142
they gave me the means.

02:22.183 --> 02:25.353
Krypton will finally
be resurrected.

02:25.395 --> 02:27.188
The defense council
will reign...

02:28.731 --> 02:32.527
And we'll have our mother
with us once again.

02:33.194 --> 02:35.697
I know you long to see her,
just as I do.

02:36.823 --> 02:38.783
Help me do that, brother.

02:41.244 --> 02:42.871
- Not like this.

02:50.211 --> 02:52.130
- The time has almost come,
Kal-El.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.882
Our people will awaken soon.

02:56.801 --> 02:58.386
And when that happens,

02:58.428 --> 03:00.972
I need you by my side,

03:01.014 --> 03:03.183
or you will be eradicated too.

03:15.653 --> 03:18.615
[heroic music]

03:18.656 --> 03:23.203
♪ ♪

03:23.244 --> 03:26.372
[insects chirping]

03:33.796 --> 03:35.632
- You finally kick him out?

03:36.466 --> 03:38.426
- Sarah, it's not
what it looks like.

03:38.468 --> 03:39.969
He wasn't at the bars.

03:40.011 --> 03:42.013
- Really?

03:42.055 --> 03:44.432
'Cause this is how things
normally go down.

03:44.474 --> 03:46.017
Just as it seems
like Dad's gonna change,

03:46.059 --> 03:47.852
he decides getting drunk
is more important

03:47.894 --> 03:49.812
than being with his family.
- That's not what happened.

03:50.313 --> 03:51.564
- Why do you always
cover for him?

03:51.606 --> 03:53.316
- I'm not covering for him.

03:53.358 --> 03:54.817
- Yes, you are.
- You know what, honey?

03:54.859 --> 03:56.236
I really can't do this
right now.

03:56.277 --> 03:57.654
- Of course you can't,

03:57.695 --> 03:59.447
'cause you just
can't accept the reality

03:59.489 --> 04:00.907
that your husband is not the
guy that you married anymore.

04:00.949 --> 04:02.242
- Enough.

04:02.283 --> 04:04.160
You don't know
what you're talking about,

04:04.202 --> 04:06.579
and I don't need a teenager

04:06.621 --> 04:07.705
telling me what to do.

04:07.747 --> 04:09.290
- [scoffs]

04:09.332 --> 04:10.375
Fine.

04:10.416 --> 04:12.460
Teenager. What do you know?

04:13.253 --> 04:14.837
I'm staying at Denise's.

04:15.713 --> 04:17.215
- Sarah!
- No!

04:17.257 --> 04:19.801
♪ ♪

04:19.842 --> 04:21.552
Sarah.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.054
[door slams]

04:23.096 --> 04:25.390
- Everything okay?

04:25.431 --> 04:28.559
- Kyle, I really need you
to tell me what happened.

04:28.601 --> 04:30.270
Everything.

04:30.311 --> 04:33.231
Starting with when
you first went to Edge.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.233
[cell phone buzzes]

04:37.568 --> 04:39.988
- Hi, you've reached Lana.
Leave a message.

04:40.029 --> 04:41.656
Have a good day.
[beeps]

04:41.698 --> 04:44.158
- Lana, you have to call me
back as soon as you can.

04:44.200 --> 04:46.911
Please. I am worried about you.

04:46.953 --> 04:48.663
[chatter]

04:48.705 --> 04:50.623
She's still not answering.

04:50.665 --> 04:52.542
- I'll send someone
to her house.

04:53.918 --> 04:57.005
[whooshes]

05:11.769 --> 05:14.230
- Morgan Edge is your brother?

05:14.272 --> 05:15.982
- There's no way, right?

05:16.024 --> 05:17.442
- He knew things about Krypton

05:17.483 --> 05:18.818
no one could possibly know.

05:18.860 --> 05:19.902
He spoke the language.

05:19.944 --> 05:21.029
He had Kryptonian powers.

05:21.070 --> 05:23.489
I...[sighing]

05:23.531 --> 05:26.159
I don't know.
- What does he want?

05:28.453 --> 05:32.999
- Kryptonians here.

05:33.041 --> 05:34.542
And for me to join him.

05:34.584 --> 05:35.752
- That's why he's putting
Kryptonian consciousness

05:35.793 --> 05:37.170
into people.

05:37.211 --> 05:38.588
- He wants Earth to become
the next Krypton.

05:38.629 --> 05:39.839
- I don't get it though.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.507
Why did he think
that you'd join him?

05:41.549 --> 05:43.676
- Because he can bring
my Kryptonian mother back.

05:44.052 --> 05:45.595
Our people.

05:45.636 --> 05:47.638
- Clark, before you go down
the rabbit's hole here,

05:47.680 --> 05:48.765
don't you think
you should find out

05:48.806 --> 05:50.808
if this is even
actually true?

05:50.850 --> 05:52.477
- I'm not gonna leave
after Edge just sent someone

05:52.518 --> 05:53.811
to kill you and Jonathan.

05:53.853 --> 05:55.855
- Babe, half the DOD's
on our front lawn.

05:55.897 --> 05:59.317
They are moving into town.
Edge is not coming here.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.527
Go, we'll call you
if we need you.

06:15.249 --> 06:18.336
[wind howling]

06:19.629 --> 06:22.423
- Is it possible?
- It is possible, yes.

06:27.095 --> 06:28.763
- How could you never tell me?

06:28.805 --> 06:30.431
- There wasn't the need.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.308
- The need?

06:32.350 --> 06:35.395
For me to know I've had a
brother here my entire life?

06:35.436 --> 06:37.105
One who wants
to restore Krypton

06:37.146 --> 06:39.399
using some technology
created by my mother?

06:39.440 --> 06:40.900
There wasn't the need?

06:40.942 --> 06:43.194
- I understand
your frustration,

06:43.236 --> 06:46.697
but restoring Krypton
was never her intent.

06:46.739 --> 06:47.949
At least not the way

06:47.990 --> 06:50.576
Zeta-Rho wished to enact it.

06:50.618 --> 06:53.287
Lara's invention was a means
of preservation,

06:53.329 --> 06:56.457
to save our people
by retaining

06:56.499 --> 06:58.126
and transferring their minds,

06:58.167 --> 07:00.294
just as my own mind
has been retained here.

07:01.295 --> 07:03.089
It was Zeta-Rho who sought

07:03.131 --> 07:05.091
to colonize other worlds

07:05.133 --> 07:08.386
and enslave their inhabitants
as hosts.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.972
- I can't let this happen.

07:11.013 --> 07:12.640
I have to bring back everyone

07:12.682 --> 07:14.183
Edge has implanted
with Kryptonian consciousness.

07:14.225 --> 07:16.727
Just tell me what to do,
and I'll do it.

07:16.769 --> 07:19.647
- The Eradicator is
well beyond my understanding.

07:19.689 --> 07:21.315
It's your mother's invention.

07:21.357 --> 07:23.776
She developed this technology.

07:24.694 --> 07:26.571
I'm sorry, my son.

07:26.612 --> 07:28.281
I cannot help you.

07:44.589 --> 07:46.132
- How come every time it seems

07:46.174 --> 07:47.842
like things
are gonna get better,

07:47.884 --> 07:49.218
something happens,

07:49.260 --> 07:50.887
and it's all just
crazier than before?

07:58.060 --> 07:59.145
You okay?

07:59.770 --> 08:01.814
- Dude, I saw footage
of what happened to Dad

08:01.856 --> 08:03.441
on John Henry's planet.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.526
He killed Mom.

08:05.568 --> 08:08.112
I mean, or her doppelganger
or whatever.

08:08.154 --> 08:09.489
- So?

08:09.530 --> 08:11.949
- So what if the Edge
from that planet

08:11.991 --> 08:13.993
is also
that Superman's brother?

08:14.035 --> 08:15.953
What if he brought back
their mom,

08:15.995 --> 08:17.997
and then he gave him
a Kryptonian family,

08:18.039 --> 08:19.916
and that's why
he turned on humanity?

08:19.957 --> 08:21.876
What if that's
what happened there...

08:23.503 --> 08:25.254
And it's happening here too?

08:28.216 --> 08:30.218
- It wouldn't change anything.

08:32.053 --> 08:34.388
- Look, all I'm saying
is going your whole life

08:34.430 --> 08:37.391
thinking that you're the only
one left in your family,

08:37.433 --> 08:39.060
and then finding out

08:39.101 --> 08:41.229
that you had a brother
that you never knew about

08:41.270 --> 08:43.147
and that you could
see your mom?

08:44.857 --> 08:47.276
That would affect anyone.
- Yeah, it would.

08:47.318 --> 08:49.278
But the difference
between Edge and your dad

08:49.320 --> 08:51.447
is that he has family:
the three of us, right here.

08:51.489 --> 08:52.907
We're his family.

08:52.949 --> 08:55.826
And no matter what happens,
we always will be.

08:55.868 --> 08:57.245
[door clicks open]

09:01.290 --> 09:03.167
- We found Kyle Cushing.

09:03.751 --> 09:05.545
- Where?

09:05.586 --> 09:07.547
- Why didn't you tell me
you were going to see Edge?

09:07.588 --> 09:09.924
- Because you lied to me, Lana,

09:09.966 --> 09:12.134
about the Executive Program.

09:12.176 --> 09:13.844
I mean, clearly you didn't
think I had what it took.

09:13.886 --> 09:14.929
- Kyle.

09:14.971 --> 09:17.431
- No, Lana, it's fine.

09:17.473 --> 09:19.725
I just sick and tired
of messing up.

09:19.767 --> 09:22.228
With you,

09:22.270 --> 09:22.853
with our girls...

09:25.273 --> 09:27.608
So yeah, I went to see him
the other morning.

09:27.650 --> 09:29.360
- And he made you an offer.

09:29.402 --> 09:31.529
- He said I could go through

09:31.571 --> 09:34.699
this process, change my life,

09:34.740 --> 09:37.368
make me better,

09:37.410 --> 09:38.744
and it did.

09:38.786 --> 09:41.247
- And what was
this process exactly?

09:41.289 --> 09:43.916
- First step was, uh,

09:43.958 --> 09:46.586
we went into this machine.

09:46.627 --> 09:49.463
- And where was that?
Where did Edge take you?

09:51.340 --> 09:53.050
[knocking]

10:00.850 --> 10:02.643
Hey, Lois.

10:02.685 --> 10:04.312
Everything okay?

10:04.353 --> 10:05.646
- Everything's fine.

10:08.649 --> 10:10.776
Just stopped by to check in.

10:10.818 --> 10:12.903
- Yes.

10:12.945 --> 10:14.572
On me.

10:15.031 --> 10:16.365
[grunts]

10:16.407 --> 10:17.825
[both heavy breathing]

10:17.867 --> 10:20.411
[laughs]
You all are so weak.

10:20.453 --> 10:22.747
[grunting]

10:23.372 --> 10:25.041
[grunts]

10:26.584 --> 10:28.085
- Not all of us.

10:28.753 --> 10:30.504
- Move, move, move, move!

10:30.546 --> 10:33.633
[tense music]

10:33.674 --> 10:37.470
♪ ♪

10:37.511 --> 10:40.598
- [grunting]

10:42.016 --> 10:43.976
- Good job.

10:46.020 --> 10:47.396
- You okay?

10:47.438 --> 10:49.482
- No. Not really.

10:54.403 --> 10:56.155
- And how are the girls?

10:56.197 --> 10:58.324
- Sophie's at my folks.
She doesn't know anything.

10:58.741 --> 11:00.117
Sarah stormed out last night.

11:00.159 --> 11:01.869
She thinks I'm covering
for Kyle.

11:01.911 --> 11:04.121
She won't answer
my calls or texts.

11:04.163 --> 11:05.831
- We'll have the boys
reach out.

11:06.415 --> 11:08.793
- You know, it has been so long

11:08.834 --> 11:11.462
since anything strange happened
in this town.

11:11.504 --> 11:13.631
I mean, I thought we were done
with this kind of stuff,

11:13.673 --> 11:16.717
and then this happens
to my husband.

11:16.759 --> 11:19.345
- Lana, we're gonna save him.
I promise.

11:19.804 --> 11:22.056
- How?
- Best place to start

11:22.098 --> 11:24.350
is by finding where Edge
hides his Eradicator.

11:24.392 --> 11:27.103
[dramatic music]

11:27.144 --> 11:29.939
- And that's the thing
they used on Kyle?

11:29.980 --> 11:33.109
- Yeah, and wherever it is,
it stands reason that location

11:33.150 --> 11:35.611
has been receiving shipments
of X-K from the Shuster mines.

11:35.653 --> 11:37.905
- What's X-K?
- X-Kryptonite.

11:37.947 --> 11:39.323
It's what Edge
has been mining for.

11:39.365 --> 11:41.200
It's what gives people
these powers.

11:41.242 --> 11:43.577
- The theory is, powers only
hold with Smallville natives,

11:43.619 --> 11:45.454
people who have had
prolonged exposure.

11:46.497 --> 11:48.874
- Like Kyle and Emily

11:48.916 --> 11:51.043
and basically
everyone I recruited

11:51.085 --> 11:52.586
for the Executive Program.

11:52.628 --> 11:55.840
- Dozens upon dozens
of what he calls subjects,

11:55.881 --> 11:57.216
his own private army.

11:57.258 --> 11:58.467
- And these people,

11:58.509 --> 12:00.177
you know their identity?

12:00.219 --> 12:02.054
- It's our murderer's row
of suspects.

12:02.096 --> 12:04.598
Info I pulled from employee
files, first hand encounters,

12:04.640 --> 12:06.016
the names you offered,

12:06.058 --> 12:07.643
anyone Edge could
have interacted with.

12:07.685 --> 12:09.562
- It's a pretty big list

12:09.603 --> 12:11.439
that unfortunately doesn't get
us closer to the big picture.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.149
- I don't have
the big picture either.

12:14.900 --> 12:17.820
Oh, I except I do see
one thing odd.

12:19.488 --> 12:20.573
Him.

12:23.868 --> 12:26.620
Dr. Dabney Donovan.

12:26.662 --> 12:29.165
Listed as Edge's
personal physician.

12:30.124 --> 12:32.752
He was the one who conducted
all the health exams

12:32.793 --> 12:35.087
for everyone
in the Executive Program.

12:35.129 --> 12:36.964
- This guy left a tenure track
position at MIT

12:37.006 --> 12:38.591
to work for Edge?

12:38.632 --> 12:40.593
- That's a pretty big salary
to walk away from.

12:40.634 --> 12:43.512
- Dual PhDs in genetics
and molecular neuro-chemistry.

12:43.554 --> 12:45.139
- Knowledge that would
come in handy

12:45.181 --> 12:46.807
if you wanted to swap
one person for another.

12:46.849 --> 12:48.851
Do you know where
these health exams took place?

12:48.893 --> 12:50.895
- No, that was top secret,

12:50.936 --> 12:53.272
and I tried to get Kyle
to tell me, before...

12:56.317 --> 12:58.652
- I think we need to try again.

13:13.125 --> 13:14.585
- Put out the APB.

13:14.627 --> 13:16.337
The entire tri-state area.

13:16.378 --> 13:19.173
Local, state, FBI, I want
the cub scouts after this guy.

13:19.924 --> 13:21.884
I figure it can't hurt to ask.

13:23.260 --> 13:25.805
At least it can't hurt me.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.306
Where is this man?

13:30.559 --> 13:33.521
- Do you even realize
the threat you now face?

13:34.355 --> 13:36.565
Of what my people will do

13:36.607 --> 13:38.567
to you and your family

13:38.609 --> 13:40.653
when the attack begins?

13:40.694 --> 13:42.446
- That's a real shame.

13:43.280 --> 13:46.116
All I wanted was
some good conversation.

13:48.577 --> 13:51.664
[whirring]
- [groaning]

13:54.124 --> 13:56.085
- One more time.

13:56.126 --> 13:58.379
Where do I find this man?

13:58.420 --> 14:01.131
- I will melt your flesh

14:01.173 --> 14:02.675
from your skull.

14:03.717 --> 14:05.344
- Not today.

14:06.595 --> 14:09.682
[whirring]
- [groaning]

14:13.561 --> 14:15.187
- Where is he?

14:20.693 --> 14:23.112
- I knew my dad was a disaster.

14:23.153 --> 14:25.531
I guess I just didn't want
to admit the extent of it.

14:25.573 --> 14:28.617
- Sarah, I'm so sorry.

14:28.659 --> 14:31.287
- Why should you be sorry?
I'm not sorry.

14:32.246 --> 14:33.497
It's better to know, right?

14:33.539 --> 14:35.666
Even if my mom's
in total denial.

14:36.417 --> 14:37.877
- Maybe you should go
a little easier on your mom.

14:37.918 --> 14:39.503
- Why?

14:39.545 --> 14:42.506
Nothing's gonna change
if my mom doesn't do something.

14:42.548 --> 14:44.633
My dad's a disaster,
and all my mom's doing

14:44.675 --> 14:47.344
is getting her black belt
in passive-aggressive texting.

14:48.387 --> 14:50.931
- You're right.
- Jon.

14:50.973 --> 14:52.933
- Sarah, the truth
about your dad is that,

14:52.975 --> 14:55.519
he is really messed up.
- Yeah, Jon, I know.

14:55.561 --> 14:57.062
- No, not from drinking.

14:57.104 --> 14:58.856
Morgan Edge
did something to him.

14:58.898 --> 15:01.775
And this is gonna sound nuts,

15:01.817 --> 15:03.611
but he's basically
been body snatched.

15:04.570 --> 15:05.988
- Body snatched?

15:06.572 --> 15:08.115
- Look, these military guys
showing up,

15:08.157 --> 15:09.867
they're from the DOD.

15:09.909 --> 15:12.703
It's a threat reduction agency
headed by our grandpa

15:12.745 --> 15:14.622
to keep the Earth
safe from aliens,

15:14.663 --> 15:16.832
and these scientists, they're
looking at your dad right now

15:16.874 --> 15:18.459
trying to help him,
but I honestly--

15:18.500 --> 15:21.420
I don't even think that
they're totally clear

15:21.462 --> 15:23.923
what's going on.
Right?

15:23.964 --> 15:26.383
So it's not their fault,

15:26.425 --> 15:28.052
and it's not his fault,

15:28.093 --> 15:31.847
and Sarah, it's definitely
not your mom's fault.

15:34.642 --> 15:36.936
- Maybe you should
go see for yourself.

15:47.905 --> 15:50.199
- Lana's really beating
herself up.

15:52.242 --> 15:53.744
- Hard not to.

15:55.496 --> 15:56.914
Clark, why would Edge

15:56.956 --> 15:59.041
give Superman time
to make a decision?

15:59.083 --> 16:00.542
- Mm, what do you mean?

16:00.584 --> 16:03.379
- Edge is a ruthless
corporate shark.

16:03.420 --> 16:05.506
He never gives anyone anything.

16:05.547 --> 16:07.132
Why give Superman time?

16:07.174 --> 16:09.718
The only reason that makes
sense is that he needs it.

16:09.760 --> 16:11.929
Maybe the Subjekts
aren't finished resurrecting

16:11.971 --> 16:13.639
or transforming
or whatever that process is

16:13.681 --> 16:15.891
because they're not done.

16:15.933 --> 16:19.728
And Edge knows that if
he's gonna defeat Superman,

16:19.770 --> 16:21.647
he needs everyone.

16:22.690 --> 16:25.693
[echoing tones]
- [muffled shouting]

16:25.734 --> 16:27.486
- They found Donovan.

16:29.613 --> 16:32.366
Huh.
I guess I'll, uh--

16:32.408 --> 16:36.036
- Go out the back?
- Go out the back, yeah.

16:42.668 --> 16:44.837
[whooshes]

16:48.090 --> 16:51.051
[dramatic music]

16:51.093 --> 16:56.348
♪ ♪

16:56.390 --> 16:58.142
You're coming with us.

17:02.396 --> 17:05.024
We need to reverse what this
machine's been doing to people.

17:05.065 --> 17:06.567
- Reverse it?
- Yeah.

17:06.608 --> 17:09.028
Turn everyone back into
the human they should be.

17:09.069 --> 17:11.280
- I can't do that.
- You'll do what I say.

17:11.321 --> 17:15.034
- Look, I barely understand
how this technology even works.

17:15.075 --> 17:16.910
If you wanna reverse
this process,

17:16.952 --> 17:18.245
you're gonna have to find

17:18.287 --> 17:19.663
whoever it is
that invented this thing.

17:19.705 --> 17:21.081
- Who the hell's that?

17:26.170 --> 17:28.255
- My mother.

17:35.804 --> 17:37.848
- All this for Morgan Edge.

17:37.890 --> 17:39.558
[dramatic music]

17:39.600 --> 17:42.019
- It's gonna get a whole lot
worse if we don't stop him.

17:42.061 --> 17:47.024
♪ ♪

17:47.066 --> 17:48.776
- He's here.

17:54.656 --> 17:55.908
- Everything okay?

17:57.034 --> 18:00.079
- Oh, I know you're used
to all this,

18:00.120 --> 18:02.331
but it's a little surreal
to see Superman

18:02.372 --> 18:03.707
in real life.

18:03.749 --> 18:06.877
I'm just so used
to watching him on TV.

18:08.337 --> 18:09.671
- Yeah, it can be
a little weird.

18:09.713 --> 18:11.006
Come on. Follow me.

18:12.049 --> 18:13.425
- Is there any way
to communicate

18:13.467 --> 18:15.385
with the consciousness
inside the Eradicator?

18:15.427 --> 18:18.347
- The Kryptonian minds inside
aren't actually alive.

18:18.388 --> 18:20.307
Once a consciousness is chosen,

18:20.349 --> 18:23.102
they need a host in order
to become activated.

18:23.143 --> 18:25.771
- So the only way this works
is to place the consciousness

18:25.813 --> 18:27.898
of Lara Lor-Van into someone
from Smallville.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.983
- That's my understanding.

18:30.025 --> 18:31.527
- Get this machine ready.

18:34.822 --> 18:36.073
- This doesn't feel right.

18:36.115 --> 18:37.324
- We don't have
any other choice.

18:37.366 --> 18:38.867
- And we're running
out of time.

18:38.909 --> 18:40.744
We need to find
a volunteer fast.

18:40.786 --> 18:42.079
- I'll do it.

18:44.915 --> 18:46.917
- Uh, I'm sorry,
but that's not possible.

18:46.959 --> 18:49.211
- Why not?
I'm from Smallville.

18:49.253 --> 18:51.338
Makes me the ideal candidate.

18:51.380 --> 18:52.798
You don't have
to look for anyone.

18:52.840 --> 18:55.509
- She does have a point.
- Dad.

18:56.718 --> 18:59.388
Can everyone just please
give us a moment alone?

18:59.429 --> 19:02.307
[somber music]

19:02.349 --> 19:09.439
♪ ♪

19:14.403 --> 19:16.071
This isn't your responsibility.

19:16.113 --> 19:17.447
- Then whose is it?

19:17.489 --> 19:19.449
I'm the one who stood by

19:19.491 --> 19:21.118
while Kyle rallied the town

19:21.160 --> 19:22.578
to Edge's side.

19:22.619 --> 19:25.747
I mean, it was me who signed up
my own friends

19:25.789 --> 19:27.332
to Edge's Executive Program.

19:27.374 --> 19:29.251
- Lana--
- This is my town,

19:29.293 --> 19:32.296
and at every critical juncture
I've failed it.

19:32.337 --> 19:34.882
So don't tell me
this isn't my responsibility.

19:34.923 --> 19:37.885
Not when I stand here
about to lose everything.

19:37.926 --> 19:39.720
- I appreciate what
you're trying to do,

19:39.761 --> 19:41.013
but you have a family.

19:41.054 --> 19:42.598
- Yeah, and my husband
is one of them,

19:42.639 --> 19:46.310
who is gonna to become
some alien psychopath

19:46.351 --> 19:47.936
if I don't do something.

19:49.021 --> 19:51.982
I have to save Kyle, Lois.

19:52.024 --> 19:54.526
If there's any chance
that he's still alive,

19:54.568 --> 19:57.529
I have to do it.
- What about Sarah and Sophie?

19:57.571 --> 19:59.740
- They mean the world to me,
you know that.

19:59.781 --> 20:01.033
- That's why I can't
let you do this.

20:01.074 --> 20:03.160
- No, it's why you have to.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.746
I have to fix this for them,

20:05.787 --> 20:08.207
for me, for everybody here.

20:08.248 --> 20:10.083
- There's no guarantee
this will even work.

20:10.125 --> 20:11.710
This is alien science.

20:11.752 --> 20:13.420
- Well, it's a good thing

20:13.462 --> 20:16.215
I'm just a local loan officer
who doesn't know any better.

20:20.427 --> 20:22.429
- You're not authorized
to go in.

20:22.471 --> 20:23.722
- This is his daughter.

20:23.764 --> 20:24.932
How much authorization
do you need?

20:24.973 --> 20:26.308
- We've been
through this already.

20:26.350 --> 20:28.101
I need you
to vacate the premises.

20:28.143 --> 20:29.102
- Or what?
What are you gonna do?

20:29.144 --> 20:30.562
Are you gonna shoot us?

20:30.604 --> 20:31.688
- Guys, maybe we should
just try again later.

20:31.730 --> 20:33.315
- No, we are going in

20:33.357 --> 20:35.317
whether GI Jerk-nuts here
wants us to or not.

20:35.359 --> 20:36.526
- The hell's going on here?

20:37.611 --> 20:39.071
I'm in the middle
of a national emergency,

20:39.112 --> 20:40.322
only to get word
my own grandsons

20:40.364 --> 20:42.115
are down here causing problems.

20:42.157 --> 20:43.700
- We're just trying to get in
so she can see her dad.

20:43.742 --> 20:45.410
- Not an option.

20:45.452 --> 20:47.037
- We already told her
what happened to him, okay?

20:47.079 --> 20:48.789
She deserves to see it
for herself.

20:50.332 --> 20:52.209
- Why would you do that?

20:52.251 --> 20:54.544
- I don't know, maybe because
I'm done with your BS secrets.

20:54.586 --> 20:56.004
- Those secrets save lives.

20:56.046 --> 20:57.631
- Really?
Because you keep saying that

20:57.673 --> 20:59.758
and it keeps proving
not to be true.

20:59.800 --> 21:01.510
- Is this about what happened
with your brother?

21:01.551 --> 21:03.804
- No, it's about everything,
okay?

21:03.845 --> 21:06.598
You keep acting like
you're doing the right thing

21:06.640 --> 21:10.143
and then it keeps proving
to be the exact opposite.

21:10.185 --> 21:12.980
[dramatic music]

21:13.021 --> 21:15.357
I mean, come on, can't you just
act like a real person for once

21:15.399 --> 21:17.609
and not a soldier?

21:17.651 --> 21:20.028
♪ ♪

21:20.070 --> 21:21.613
- Let 'em in.

21:27.494 --> 21:29.288
- Thanks, Grandpa.

21:34.751 --> 21:35.877
- Dad?

21:41.508 --> 21:42.968
I don't get it.

21:43.010 --> 21:45.012
You said that there'd
be some kind of...

21:46.596 --> 21:48.307
- You.

21:51.059 --> 21:52.769
You think your little toys
can stop us?

21:52.811 --> 21:54.396
- Dad.

21:54.438 --> 21:56.606
- Dad?

21:56.648 --> 21:59.609
Oh, Daddy doesn't exist
anymore.

21:59.651 --> 22:01.695
He's a screaming corpse.

22:01.737 --> 22:04.489
Ashes on the pyre.
[laughs]

22:04.531 --> 22:06.491
- Hey, Sarah, let's just--
let's just get out of here.

22:06.533 --> 22:09.745
Hey, hey, hey,
come on, come on, come on.

22:11.496 --> 22:12.622
- Hey.

22:14.374 --> 22:16.752
When I get out of here,

22:16.793 --> 22:19.588
I'm gonna kill you first.

22:26.053 --> 22:27.846
- I don't like this.
- I don't like it either,

22:27.888 --> 22:29.765
but it's her choice,
and we have to respect it.

22:29.806 --> 22:31.099
- I know, but it's Lana.

22:31.141 --> 22:32.434
She's one
of my closest friends.

22:32.476 --> 22:34.061
- Which is why
you should say something,

22:34.102 --> 22:36.563
even if it's as you,
it'll mean a lot.

22:37.522 --> 22:40.484
[somber music]

22:40.525 --> 22:47.616
♪ ♪

22:53.622 --> 22:55.082
- [sighs]

23:01.505 --> 23:04.091
- I wanted to thank you.

23:04.132 --> 23:05.133
It's very brave.

23:05.175 --> 23:06.510
- I wouldn't be so sure.

23:06.551 --> 23:09.721
My heart is racing
a million miles an hour.

23:09.763 --> 23:12.682
- Yeah, I, um, I know.

23:12.724 --> 23:14.059
- Right.
[laughs]

23:14.101 --> 23:15.519
Sorry.

23:15.560 --> 23:17.104
- You know,
you don't have to do this.

23:18.730 --> 23:20.190
There's always another way.

23:20.232 --> 23:22.150
- I don't think
you really believe that.

23:23.735 --> 23:25.737
Also did Superman
just lie to me?

23:25.779 --> 23:28.490
- It's not lying.
I'm just, uh...

23:28.532 --> 23:30.075
I'm just an optimist.

23:30.117 --> 23:32.119
- I guess that's
what makes you a hero.

23:32.160 --> 23:34.329
- You're the hero
right now, Lana.

23:39.209 --> 23:40.627
- It's time.

24:15.871 --> 24:17.539
We'll be right here.

24:31.094 --> 24:34.181
[machine whirring]

24:52.532 --> 24:54.493
Did it work?
Is she okay?

24:56.703 --> 24:58.163
- [gasps]

24:58.205 --> 25:01.166
[hopeful music]

25:01.208 --> 25:08.298
♪ ♪

25:09.591 --> 25:11.343
Kal-El.

25:15.472 --> 25:16.890
- Mother.

25:22.103 --> 25:25.190
[machine whirring]

25:25.232 --> 25:27.442
- I know this must be
a lot to process.

25:27.484 --> 25:30.737
- Resurrection was
my life's work,

25:30.779 --> 25:33.281
as a way to ensure
our civilization

25:33.323 --> 25:34.824
was not lost forever.

25:34.866 --> 25:36.201
[dramatic music]

25:36.243 --> 25:38.411
It was never meant to be used
as a way

25:38.453 --> 25:40.956
to supplant another race.

25:40.997 --> 25:43.333
Kryptonians
are peaceful people.

25:43.375 --> 25:44.793
♪ ♪

25:44.834 --> 25:47.003
At least the majority of us.

25:47.045 --> 25:48.922
- I don't understand.

25:50.507 --> 25:54.594
Zeta-Rho, my brother?

25:56.429 --> 25:57.973
You had another family?

25:58.473 --> 26:01.059
- We were genetically matched.

26:01.101 --> 26:03.103
That's how unions were formed

26:03.144 --> 26:05.230
for thousands of years
on Krypton...

26:06.898 --> 26:08.567
And then I met your father.

26:09.693 --> 26:11.528
We fell in love

26:11.570 --> 26:14.906
and ended my relationship
with Zeta-Rho.

26:14.948 --> 26:17.242
Jor-El and I shared a vision

26:17.284 --> 26:19.619
for a better world.

26:19.661 --> 26:21.246
I gave birth to you.

26:21.288 --> 26:23.915
And then your father and I,

26:23.957 --> 26:27.669
when we decided
to send you to Earth,

26:27.711 --> 26:30.046
we hoped you would
live that vision.

26:30.088 --> 26:31.298
- I think I have.

26:31.339 --> 26:34.301
[warm music]

26:34.342 --> 26:35.552
♪ ♪

26:35.594 --> 26:38.847
The sunstone crystal
in my pod,

26:38.888 --> 26:40.307
why only father's?

26:40.348 --> 26:41.766
Why not yours as well?

26:41.808 --> 26:44.144
- It was stolen by Zeta-Rho.

26:45.395 --> 26:47.397
Revenge for leaving him.

26:47.439 --> 26:49.816
My biggest fear
in letting you go

26:49.858 --> 26:52.569
was that you would be
without a mother.

26:52.611 --> 26:54.154
- I had a mother here.

26:55.530 --> 26:57.073
Her name was Martha.

26:59.951 --> 27:02.662
She loved me very much.

27:02.704 --> 27:06.291
- You have no idea how much
that means to me, Kal-El.

27:07.751 --> 27:10.045
This world,

27:10.086 --> 27:12.505
it welcomed you.

27:12.547 --> 27:14.466
- It has.

27:14.507 --> 27:17.594
- And you found someone.

27:17.636 --> 27:20.263
I can tell
by how you look at her.

27:20.305 --> 27:21.848
- [laughs]

27:26.102 --> 27:28.188
She's the love of my life.

27:28.229 --> 27:30.231
- It's all
I ever wanted for you.

27:31.816 --> 27:34.235
To find a new home,

27:34.277 --> 27:36.655
someone to love,

27:36.696 --> 27:39.115
create a family of your own.

27:39.908 --> 27:41.534
- We have two sons.

27:44.371 --> 27:46.498
- Tell me all about them.

27:56.007 --> 27:58.134
- What are we gonna do?

27:58.176 --> 27:59.886
- We?

27:59.928 --> 28:01.554
Look at her.
She's upset.

28:01.596 --> 28:03.807
I think she wants
to talk to you.

28:03.848 --> 28:05.225
- Yeah, and why's she upset?

28:05.266 --> 28:06.559
Because you had to tell her
what's going on.

28:06.601 --> 28:08.103
- Hey, look,
I'm not gonna apologize

28:08.144 --> 28:10.605
for telling the truth, okay?
Ever.

28:10.647 --> 28:15.777
And I wish things weren't
the way they are,

28:15.819 --> 28:19.197
and what happened to her dad,
it really sucks.

28:19.239 --> 28:21.783
Right?
But I think--

28:21.825 --> 28:24.285
I think all you can do now
is be there for her.

28:24.327 --> 28:26.287
- Yeah.
You're right.

28:45.890 --> 28:47.684
I'm so sorry.

28:47.726 --> 28:49.477
- I had to see him.

28:49.519 --> 28:51.771
I had to understand,
but now it's like,

28:51.813 --> 28:54.023
I don't even know
what that was.

28:54.065 --> 28:56.317
- I think a lot
of really smart people

28:56.359 --> 28:57.652
are trying to figure that out
right now.

29:01.281 --> 29:04.033
- Last night, that--

29:04.075 --> 29:06.161
that was my dad.

29:06.202 --> 29:07.871
I know that was my dad,

29:07.912 --> 29:12.083
but I was awful to him.

29:12.125 --> 29:13.793
I guess that could be
the last time

29:13.835 --> 29:15.462
I ever see my dad.

29:16.755 --> 29:18.131
Was calling my dad drunk

29:18.173 --> 29:20.759
gonna be the last thing
I ever say to him?

29:25.805 --> 29:27.640
I need him back.

29:32.270 --> 29:34.689
- We're just gonna
have to hold onto hope.

29:48.369 --> 29:50.497
- I'll find them.
- There's no need.

29:50.538 --> 29:51.706
- They have the Eradic--

29:51.748 --> 29:55.168
- I said there's no need!
[sighs]

29:55.210 --> 29:56.461
[dramatic music]

29:56.503 --> 29:59.130
Leave and prepare
for our arrival.

29:59.172 --> 30:00.340
- Now?

30:00.381 --> 30:03.760
♪ ♪

30:03.802 --> 30:05.178
- Kal-El made his decision.

30:05.220 --> 30:07.639
He chose humanity over us.

30:09.265 --> 30:11.726
There's no saving
my brother now.

30:20.693 --> 30:22.445
- How does this thing work?

30:25.156 --> 30:27.408
- The same principle
as a computer.

30:27.450 --> 30:29.744
In this case,
instead of a computer,

30:29.786 --> 30:31.120
it's a brain,

30:31.162 --> 30:33.414
and the information
being uploaded

30:33.456 --> 30:35.208
is a person's consciousness.

30:35.250 --> 30:39.212
The Eradicator holds
and transfers this information,

30:39.254 --> 30:42.131
a new consciousness,
into a person.

30:42.173 --> 30:45.635
- So during
this transfer process,

30:45.677 --> 30:48.221
does the old consciousness
exist?

30:48.263 --> 30:51.641
- It does
until the transfer is complete.

30:51.683 --> 30:53.935
- And then the new
consciousness fully takes over.

30:53.977 --> 30:55.144
- How long does that take?

30:55.186 --> 30:57.689
- Days. Weeks.

30:57.730 --> 30:59.732
Depends how willing the host is

30:59.774 --> 31:01.860
to accept this new life,
if at all.

31:01.901 --> 31:04.445
- But the Kryptonian part
that's developing,

31:04.487 --> 31:06.739
that person can just emerge
at any time?

31:06.781 --> 31:09.325
- If prompted, yes.

31:09.367 --> 31:12.161
The Kryptonian consciousness
will remain in the Eradicator,

31:12.203 --> 31:15.039
and their powers
will dissipate over time.

31:15.081 --> 31:16.374
- Then how do we stop this?

31:16.416 --> 31:18.710
- Prevent the transfer
from completing,

31:18.751 --> 31:21.588
so only the old consciousness
remains.

31:21.629 --> 31:23.464
- Can we do that?
- We can.

31:23.506 --> 31:25.675
We just need to get the people
who were affected

31:25.717 --> 31:28.428
to go through the eradication
process again.

31:28.469 --> 31:30.722
- Bring them here? All of them?
- Yes.

31:30.763 --> 31:31.973
- And run them
through the machine?

31:32.015 --> 31:33.433
- Yes.
- But we don't know

31:33.474 --> 31:35.351
how many people
have gone through this.

31:35.393 --> 31:37.353
- There has to be another way
to do it all at once.

31:37.395 --> 31:39.606
- That would require
too much energy.

31:39.647 --> 31:41.024
- How much?

31:41.065 --> 31:42.483
- We would need something

31:42.525 --> 31:44.819
that rivals this planet's sun.

31:45.778 --> 31:48.072
[machine whirrs]

31:48.114 --> 31:51.534
[ears ringing]

31:51.576 --> 31:53.077
- It's Edge.

31:54.287 --> 31:55.580
Figure out a way
to do everyone at once.

31:55.622 --> 31:56.998
I'll hold them off
as long as I can.

31:57.040 --> 31:58.499
- How the hell
are you gonna do that?

31:58.541 --> 32:00.710
- Appeal to him the same way
he did to you...

32:01.878 --> 32:03.171
As a brother.

32:06.341 --> 32:07.425
- Mother.

32:07.467 --> 32:10.053
- Go, my son.

32:10.094 --> 32:12.972
Be the hero
I knew you would be.

32:31.741 --> 32:33.076
- Hello again...

32:34.494 --> 32:37.747
Superman.

32:44.462 --> 32:45.421
- Why do you love them?

32:45.463 --> 32:47.423
There must be a reason.

32:47.465 --> 32:49.175
Did they take you in

32:49.217 --> 32:51.219
when you first arrived?

32:51.260 --> 32:53.012
Did they treat you
like you were one of them?

32:53.054 --> 32:56.265
[dramatic music]

32:56.307 --> 32:57.850
'Cause they did
no such thing for me.

32:57.892 --> 33:00.061
I landed in
the British countryside,

33:00.103 --> 33:01.479
where I was not greeted.

33:01.521 --> 33:02.772
[gunshot]

33:02.814 --> 33:04.732
[group shouting]
I was hunted.

33:07.944 --> 33:09.112
[gasps]

33:14.283 --> 33:15.868
Trapped.

33:15.910 --> 33:17.161
[somber music]

33:17.203 --> 33:18.454
Caught.

33:18.496 --> 33:19.872
♪ ♪

33:19.914 --> 33:21.165
And kept hidden from the world

33:21.207 --> 33:22.291
for years.

33:23.042 --> 33:25.670
A piece of alien meat,

33:25.712 --> 33:27.296
an experiment

33:27.338 --> 33:29.924
for them to learn
why I had abilities.

33:29.966 --> 33:32.301
- Brother, I am sorry
that happened to you...

33:33.803 --> 33:35.680
But not everyone here
is like that.

33:37.348 --> 33:39.100
- Only when they're afraid.

33:40.893 --> 33:43.896
And believe me,

33:43.938 --> 33:45.690
I made them afraid.

33:45.732 --> 33:48.693
[dramatic music]

33:48.735 --> 33:55.825
♪ ♪

33:58.745 --> 34:00.288
[high pitched humming]

34:00.329 --> 34:02.165
No.
No.

34:02.206 --> 34:03.624
No!

34:05.626 --> 34:07.587
And I'm going to again

34:07.628 --> 34:10.673
without you, brother.

34:10.715 --> 34:17.805
♪ ♪

34:22.977 --> 34:25.229
- Tell me.

34:27.023 --> 34:29.650
What is it like
being with my son?

34:29.692 --> 34:32.236
- Most of the time, it's easy.

34:32.278 --> 34:35.156
And sometimes
it's very difficult.

34:37.241 --> 34:38.993
Most of the time,
I feel very secure,

34:39.035 --> 34:41.829
and then I've also had
some of the most...

34:41.871 --> 34:44.165
terrifying days
in my entire life.

34:45.666 --> 34:50.046
But there's always love
and respect.

34:50.880 --> 34:52.256
- A partnership?

34:52.298 --> 34:54.217
- Very much so.

34:54.258 --> 34:56.094
[soft music]

34:56.135 --> 34:59.180
[beeping]

34:59.222 --> 35:00.932
♪ ♪

35:00.973 --> 35:02.600
- On Krypton, I had

35:02.642 --> 35:05.853
all the hopes and dreams
one could ever have.

35:05.895 --> 35:07.438
And I lived them all.

35:07.480 --> 35:09.357
And then one day,

35:09.398 --> 35:12.777
those hopes and dreams
were for the son I just had.

35:12.819 --> 35:15.696
♪ ♪

35:15.738 --> 35:17.448
Thank you, Lois,

35:17.490 --> 35:19.659
for making them come true.

35:19.700 --> 35:22.995
- He's this world's first
and greatest hero,

35:23.037 --> 35:26.707
but I want you to know
that he's an even better man.

35:26.749 --> 35:30.044
♪ ♪

35:30.086 --> 35:31.754
- About last night

35:31.796 --> 35:33.131
and the performance,

35:33.172 --> 35:35.716
I'm so sorry I didn't make it.

35:38.678 --> 35:40.847
- It was because of this,
wasn't it?

35:41.597 --> 35:43.099
- Yeah.

35:43.141 --> 35:45.935
- [sighing]

35:45.977 --> 35:48.938
I feel like such a jerk,
Jordan.

35:48.980 --> 35:52.108
All this weirdness with you,
and now it makes sense.

35:52.150 --> 35:55.319
I mean,
you knew all about all of this,

35:55.361 --> 35:56.863
and you had
to keep it a secret.

35:56.904 --> 35:59.240
[warm music]

35:59.282 --> 36:00.700
- You know,
I'm actually really glad

36:00.741 --> 36:02.660
that your dad was there
instead of me.

36:02.702 --> 36:04.078
♪ ♪

36:04.120 --> 36:06.289
You guys got to
have that together.

36:06.330 --> 36:08.207
It's a great memory
to hold onto.

36:10.334 --> 36:11.878
- Here you go.

36:13.754 --> 36:16.716
[dramatic music]

36:16.757 --> 36:18.050
- Something's going on.

36:18.092 --> 36:20.219
♪ ♪

36:20.261 --> 36:23.347
[chatter]

36:25.975 --> 36:27.351
- The hell?

36:40.531 --> 36:41.824
[siren wailing]

36:41.866 --> 36:43.618
- Yes, humans are flawed,

36:43.659 --> 36:46.078
and yes, some more than others,

36:46.120 --> 36:48.497
but they don't deserve
what you're trying to do.

36:48.539 --> 36:50.499
- You will defend them
over your own kind?

36:50.541 --> 36:52.752
- They don't deserve
to lose their lives.

36:52.793 --> 36:55.046
- They are inferior to us, Kal.

36:55.087 --> 36:56.964
- No, they're not.
They're just different.

36:57.006 --> 36:58.716
- I was sent here
with a mission

36:58.758 --> 37:01.510
to resurrect my people.
- No.

37:01.552 --> 37:03.554
- To save Krypton.
- Stop.

37:03.596 --> 37:05.264
- And I will not fail.

37:05.306 --> 37:06.557
- Yes, you will.

37:06.599 --> 37:08.100
- The thing is, Kal,

37:08.142 --> 37:10.561
this is the only planet
you've ever known,

37:10.603 --> 37:13.356
so you don't know the pain
of losing one,

37:13.397 --> 37:15.399
but I do,

37:15.441 --> 37:18.486
and I am not going
to let that happen again.

37:21.280 --> 37:23.074
And neither are they.

37:26.077 --> 37:29.163
[whooshing]

37:35.670 --> 37:37.588
[dramatic music]

37:37.630 --> 37:39.423
- That's your family coming,
Kal.

37:39.465 --> 37:41.968
Your real people,
your real heritage.

37:42.009 --> 37:44.053
Make a choice.

37:44.095 --> 37:46.264
Us or them?

37:46.305 --> 37:49.684
♪ ♪

37:49.725 --> 37:52.061
- There is no us or them.

38:11.455 --> 38:13.291
Sam, we're out of time.

38:13.332 --> 38:14.542
Is it ready?

38:17.086 --> 38:19.922
- Ready?
- We are.

38:19.964 --> 38:21.674
- It is,

38:21.716 --> 38:24.176
except for that
energy source part.

38:24.218 --> 38:26.262
We don't have anything
strong enough here.

38:26.304 --> 38:27.263
- Yes, we do. Me.

38:27.305 --> 38:28.764
- What?

38:28.806 --> 38:30.308
- I'll release all my energy
at once,

38:30.349 --> 38:32.184
create a solar flare;
it'll be enough.

38:32.226 --> 38:33.894
- And you'll be out
of commission for days.

38:33.936 --> 38:35.062
I can't let you do this.

38:35.104 --> 38:36.439
- We don't have a choice.

38:36.480 --> 38:38.274
- Superman.

38:38.316 --> 38:39.900
- Sam, we're out of time.
Get everyone out.

38:39.942 --> 38:41.319
I'm coming in
and so are they.

38:41.360 --> 38:42.695
- Everyone out!

38:42.737 --> 38:44.238
Go, now!

38:44.280 --> 38:45.323
Go! Out!

38:45.364 --> 38:47.116
Now! Go, go, go!

39:03.299 --> 39:04.842
- Boys, boys!

39:04.884 --> 39:06.344
Please come now!

39:06.385 --> 39:08.179
- Where's Sarah?
- I don't know.

39:08.596 --> 39:10.222
- [grunts]

39:10.264 --> 39:13.351
[grunting]

39:26.572 --> 39:28.157
- Boys, right now!

39:29.408 --> 39:30.826
- Run!

39:42.046 --> 39:43.672
- Come on, come on.

39:54.350 --> 39:56.060
- Stop!

40:00.398 --> 40:04.652
- [screaming]

40:15.579 --> 40:18.541
[somber music]

40:18.582 --> 40:25.673
♪ ♪

40:38.644 --> 40:40.354
- Sarah?

40:41.272 --> 40:42.440
- Dad?

40:43.941 --> 40:45.985
Dad?

40:46.026 --> 40:47.611
- Mija, what happened?

41:01.542 --> 41:03.127
- [sighs]

41:04.753 --> 41:07.840
[chatter and shouting]

41:23.689 --> 41:24.815
- Lana?

41:26.233 --> 41:27.735
- Lois.

41:38.913 --> 41:40.748
- [laughs]

41:43.083 --> 41:44.627
- [laughs]

41:50.424 --> 41:52.760
- Sir, no sign of Morgan Edge.

41:52.801 --> 41:55.054
- Search the globe
until you find him.

41:56.347 --> 41:57.890
- There's no sign
of Dad either.

41:58.849 --> 42:00.059
- Where is he?

42:10.694 --> 42:13.781
- [panting]

42:31.632 --> 42:34.593
[dramatic music]

42:34.635 --> 42:41.725
♪ ♪

42:47.690 --> 42:49.525
[whooshing]

42:50.776 --> 42:52.403
- Just us?

42:52.444 --> 42:54.613
- For now.

42:54.655 --> 42:56.740
But all is not lost.

43:18.345 --> 43:21.307
[dramatic music]

43:21.348 --> 43:28.439
♪ ♪

43:37.364 --> 43:40.451
- Greg, move your head.
